					<h1 class="text-center">Setup</h1>

					<p>Kraken is built with <a href="http://gulpjs.com/">gulp.js</a> and <a href="http://sass-lang.com/">powered by Sass</a>, an extension of CSS that adds powerful features like variables and functions and makes customizing Kraken a lot easier. If you don't use Gulp or Sass, that's ok. Kraken comes with compiled vanilla CSS and JS, too.</p>

					<ul>
						<li><a data-scroll href="#structure">What's Included</a></li>
						<li><a data-scroll href="#sass">Sass</a></li>
						<li><a data-scroll href="#css">Vanilla CSS</a></li>
						<li><a data-scroll href="#html">HTML Template</a></li>
					</ul>

					<hr>


					<h2 id="structure">What's Included</h2>

					<p>Compiled and production-ready code can be found in the <code>dist</code> directory. The <code>src</code> directory contains development code. Unit tests are located in the <code>test</code> directory.</p>

